## About Warqube
Warqube analyses your [WARC files](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WARC_(file_format)) and presents the results in a local dashboard webapp. Warqube is build in R programming language with some Python and SQL thrown in. It uses [JHOVE](https://jhove.openpreservation.org/) for valdiation and characterisation, [WARCIO](https://github.com/webrecorder/warcio) for indexing the content and [pywb](https://github.com/webrecorder/pywb) for playback. Under the hood it uses [DuckDB](https://duckdb.org/) as an analytical processing database. The data is stored in a .duckdb file for reuse in later sessions.

## Features

- WARC validation
- Policy checking
- Pywb playback
- PII detection

